3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Spatially-coupled codes have applications in communication systems, which fall under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses a type of code that can be used in networks, which could fall under the domain of social and information networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a modified version of spatially-coupled codes, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms for encoding and decoding.
